Subject: Previous debt and new order



Good morning Karen



I=92m sure I don=92t have to explain the basic rules of running a successfu=
l business with you; however, the two most important concepts are:



  *   Always make sure that your suppliers are paid timeously.



Failure to pay your suppliers results in no further supplies and with nothi=
ng to sell the enterprise will fail.  RegimA UK does receive a very generou=
s cost price from RegimA SA which when compared to the selling price in the=
 UK should produce a healthy profit after all business costs are deducted.



Now I realise that Isaac left us with a substantial amount of debt and cost=
ly long-term agreements that we had to honour, but this burden was surely p=
aid off some time ago.



Make sure your cost of sales are priced as far below your actual sales as p=
ossible.



The wider this margin is the more profitable the enterprise will be.



As an enterprise grows, more sophisticated financial tools are needed to ma=
nage it properly.  However, if these running costs are such that they excee=
d the income generated, then the enterprise will surely fail.



I suspect that the inability of RegimA UK to pay RegimA SA for product is d=
ue to the above inequality and I will need some information from you to asc=
ertain whether or not this is the case.



I would need the following information:



One year=92s bank statements on all the major bank accounts where the clien=
ts pay into, as well as any saving accounts linked to this main account.



Financial statements for all the companies for the last 4 years.



I need to see proof that the VAT, PAYE and company income taxes were submit=
ted timeously and are all paid up to date.



I need to know if any suppliers and customers account are overdue.



List of all salaries.



List of all regular outgoings i.e. subscriptions, apps, financial accountin=
g packages etc.



Your current price lists for all the products.



Obviously, you will need help and input from all Regima UK staff in order t=
o complete this task.



I have attached the previous product and freight invoices, which totals =A3=
41 184.



I have attached the estimated invoice for your new order which totals =A313=
 683, and this is excluding the freight costs.



Hope to receive the requested information soonest.



Regards





